<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 06 at 4:25PM CDT  by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Ashley
County through 500 PM CDT...
At 425 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Snyder, or 11 miles east of Hamburg. This storm was nearly
stationary.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Portland, Montrose, Parkdale and Snyder.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
